cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes a nonlinear distance metric learning scheme that can benefit k-NN classification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on synthetic and real datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of Lie transformation groups and geodesic interpolation suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on distance metrics and spatially varying metrics suggests that it may also belong to the scientific computing (cs.SD) sub-category.
